You can access the data through a json file, using the employees_data.json file, 
& through a Postgres database through a self-made database or the cloud hosted supabase;

Enter the application using the details in samplelogin.



Package Flow:

1. model: 1. Employee constructor
	
2. main: 1. Main class -> Calls 'controller.MainMenu' to display menu.

3. controller: -> Calls all 'service' package.
				 1. MainMenu -> Has choices to select a file system/a postgres db. 
				(Change the dbMenu "connect_to_db" as per the use case, details mentioned).
				(For a local postgres db, follow the commands in "src/main/resources/SqlQueriesToRunDB")
				Also calls service.LoginAndAccess for loggin in.
				2. AdminMenu -> Displays the Menu of an Admin.
				3. ManagerMenu -> Displays the Menu of a Manager.
				4. EmployeeMenu -> Displays the Menu of an Employee.
				
4. service: Take login values, input values and perform validation. -> Calls 'dao' package.
				1. LoginAndAccess -> 1. Checks validation of user and their role, for Menu access.
				1. Create -> Methods to Create a new user.
				2. Read -> Methods to read data of one or more employees.
				3. Update -> Methods to Update several fields of an employee.
				4. Delete -> Methods to delete data of an employee.
				5. PasswordTableDB -> Accessed by Create to add password of the newly created employee in the passwords table.
				6. RoleTableDB -> Accessed by Create to add roles of the newly created employee in the roles table.
				7. SetNextID -> Called by Create to add an auto generated ID to the new user.
				8. PasswordMethods -> Get details of loggedIn user, Check roles, Hash Password, ResetPassword, UpdatePassword, Create default password.
				
5. dao: Implements all methods called by "service"
				1. CrudInterface -> Contains formats and rules of data.
				1. CrudImplementation -> Implements the CrudInterface, and performs actual data manipulation.
				3. EmployeeListOps -> Performs operations on the EmployeeList containing all employees' data.
				4. SaveEmployeesToFile -> Saves the EmployeeList to the file.
				
6. util: Contains validations metrics
				1. MakeConnection -> Checks and performs PostgreSQL database connection.
				2. ValidateId -> Validates the Id of the user on whom data manipulation is to take place.
				3. ValidPassword -> Checks the password pattern when ccreated manually.
				
7.  enums -> contains enums for several parts of the project.

8. customExceptions -> Contains custom exceptions.
				 